1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,500
Interviewer: In the first moments of entering the room

2
00:00:02,541 --> 00:00:04,791
Tell me what was in your mind

3
00:00:05,041 --> 00:00:09,291
I thought they were going to execute me

4
00:00:11,541 --> 00:00:12,625
That is what I felt

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,625
It was all terror and fear

6
00:00:16,791 --> 00:00:19,916
Because every little while you hear they took someone

7
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:24,250
He might be a policeman for example, and they kill him

8
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:26,125
Another for something else, for many reasons

9
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:30,416
So I thought I would be one of the victims and be killed

10
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:33,750
I imagined I would die like them

11
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:37,416
Interviewer: How many people were with you in this room?

12
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:40,166
At first I was alone

13
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:43,125
Then a boy named Edmond came in

14
00:00:43,958 --> 00:00:45,916
A Christian, as if he had converted to Islam

15
00:00:46,541 --> 00:00:47,625
He stayed two days with me

16
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:52,875
Later on every two or three days they would bring one or two

17
00:00:52,875 --> 00:00:58,291
He would sit two or three hours then they would transfer him

18
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,500
Interviewer: Regarding the person you mentioned

19
00:01:01,541 --> 00:01:03,375
Edmond the Christian

20
00:01:03,958 --> 00:01:06,666
How did they treat him?

21
00:01:06,958 --> 00:01:08,666
Their treatment was good

22
00:01:09,666 --> 00:01:11,625
Interviewer: Didn’t you learn what his charge was?

23
00:01:11,625 --> 00:01:14,250
Since he was asked to surrender

24
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:15,541
And he did, why arrest him?

25
00:01:16,041 --> 00:01:17,125
I was afraid to ask him

26
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:19,750
Interviewer: Didn’t you talk about this?

27
00:01:19,791 --> 00:01:24,000
I was afraid because they listened to us through the windows

28
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:27,875
They walked around the yard, so we were scared to talk

29
00:01:28,875 --> 00:01:31,666
Interviewer: Didn’t he try to ask you or talk with you?

30
00:01:31,666 --> 00:01:33,250
No, he didn’t ask me

31
00:01:33,958 --> 00:01:37,541
Interviewer: Did he show signs of torture?

32
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:40,791
No, no, he didn’t show any signs of torture

33
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,250
Interviewer: Didn’t they use any means of torture on him?

34
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:45,375
No, he stayed two days with me

35
00:01:45,916 --> 00:01:47,958
Then they transferred him, and I don’t know where they took him

36
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:49,833
Interviewer: Where was he from?

37
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:54,875
I asked him, Are you from Mosul? He said, Yes

38
00:01:55,416 --> 00:01:59,041
I still remember he was from the Aden neighborhood

39
00:01:59,125 --> 00:02:01,250
He told me he lived in the Aden neighborhood

40
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:04,875
And his family had all fled to Erbil

41
00:02:05,916 --> 00:02:07,125
And he had stayed here alone

42
00:02:07,416 --> 00:02:09,291
Interviewer: Didn’t you ask him why he’d stayed?

43
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:12,166
I told you I was afraid to ask him

44
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:15,125
I was afraid to ask him

45
00:02:15,250 --> 00:02:17,666
Because it’s possible he was with them

46
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:20,625
Interviewer: So you stayed here 28 days

47
00:02:20,791 --> 00:02:22,958
And most of the time you were alone

48
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,791
Interviewer: In this room or cell
Witness: Yes

49
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:27,791
Interviewer: How did you spend your time here?

50
00:02:28,541 --> 00:02:33,250
My time was harsh, a day felt like a year

51
00:02:35,125 --> 00:02:39,125
Interviewer: Didn’t they leave you something specific to use?

52
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:42,125
Like prayers, since you were so close to death

53
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:45,250
Interviewer: Were there Qurans in the prison?
Witness: Yes

54
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:47,916
Interviewer: You mean they allowed them?
Witness: Yes, yes

55
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:50,666
I had a Quran to read and I prayed normally

56
00:02:52,625 --> 00:02:55,375
I made <i>duaa</i> [supplication] and prayed

57
00:02:55,416 --> 00:02:58,750
I fulfilled my duty of worshipping God Almighty

58
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:04,125
I prayed to God to free me, to let me out and get rid of them

59
00:03:05,125 --> 00:03:06,250
Interviewer: How did you spend the night?

60
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:08,000
I spent it terrified

61
00:03:09,416 --> 00:03:10,500
It was all horror and fear

62
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:15,916
Interviewer: While you were in this room at night

63
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:20,000
Did you imagine they would come to you?

64
00:03:20,041 --> 00:03:23,833
Yes, I imagined they would come to me

65
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:25,625
Interviewer: Can you describe this state to us?

66
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:29,125
I imagined it to myself

67
00:03:29,166 --> 00:03:31,166
I told myself that after 10 minutes

68
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,500
Or after an hour or two or at midnight

69
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,375
They would call me, take me, and execute me

70
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:37,875
Just like the others they executed

71
00:03:39,875 --> 00:03:42,250
They planted horror and fear in my heart

72
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,541
And this continues even now, as I talk to you

73
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:48,916
As I speak with you now, I feel they are here

74
00:03:50,666 --> 00:03:53,250
Interviewer: Did you sleep very little?
Witness: Yes, very little

75
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,541
Interviewer: Do you mean because of overthinking and fear?

76
00:03:55,541 --> 00:03:57,541
Yes, it is the thinking that exhausted me

77
00:03:57,541 --> 00:04:01,125
And I still take psychiatric medication to this day

78
00:04:01,375 --> 00:04:03,916
Interviewer: Given that you were alone in this place

79
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:08,000
Did you find yourself not wanting to sleep out of fear

80
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:09,250
That they would execute you while you slept?

81
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:12,000
Yes, I felt afraid

82
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:14,791
Interviewer: So you tried not to sleep?

83
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:18,875
Yes, I tried not to sleep for fear they would kill me while I slept

84
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:22,250
Interviewer: Was that imagination?

85
00:04:22,291 --> 00:04:25,250
Or did it reflect a real feeling inside you?

86
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:27,166
It was a real feeling

87
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:31,541
Interviewer: Have you heard of such a thing happening?

88
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:33,250
Yes, they executed many people

89
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,041
There’s the Khasfa sinkhole

90
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:37,875
How many innocent people they threw into it

91
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,833
More than 5,000, maybe up to 10,000

92
00:04:43,666 --> 00:04:47,958
Interviewer: You were alone, so surely you stayed silent the whole time

93
00:04:48,375 --> 00:04:51,541
Did you have moments when you reflected during detention?

94
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:55,250
Did you remember things and then sit and cry?

95
00:04:55,375 --> 00:05:00,541
Yes, I cried, I did not feel relief except after I’d cried

96
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:04,291
Interviewer: Did this happen often?
Witness: Yes, very often

97
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,833
Very often, about once or twice daily

98
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:09,541
I remembered my children and my wife

99
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:12,125
I said to myself, I will not see them anymore

100
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:17,125
Because they will execute me and my story will end

101
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:21,916
And all my thoughts were of my children, my wife, and my home

102
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:30,125
Interviewer: While you were in solitary confinement for 28 days

103
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:33,000
Except for two nights when the Christian was with you

104
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:36,291
How did they treat you throughout this period?

105
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:40,250
It was ordinary treatment

106
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:44,041
Interviewer: Was their speech harsh?

107
00:05:44,166 --> 00:05:47,125
There was shouting and so on

108
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:50,833
Like, come here and go there, in a shouting tone

109
00:05:51,166 --> 00:05:52,500
And sometimes not

110
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:55,750
They would tell me, for example, get up, Abu Abd al-Rahman, it is time for prayer

111
00:05:56,791 --> 00:06:00,291
Interviewer: Did this treatment differ from one jailer to another?

112
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:01,666
Yes, it did, that is true

113
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:04,375
Interviewer: So there was a jailer who respected you and called you Abu Abd al-Rahman?

114
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:06,125
Yes, there were those who called me that

115
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,625
Some of them respected me, and some did not

116
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:09,958
Interviewer: Which jailers were more respectful to you?

117
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,125
Those who were from Mosul

118
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,500
Interviewer: Do you mean Mosul residents affiliated with them?

119
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:15,250
Yes, from Mosul, they were respectful

120
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:19,666
But the Arabs from the districts and subdistricts were not respectful

121
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:22,875
They had all come out of prisons

122
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:26,500
Their bodies were tattooed, and so on

123
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:29,125
Interviewer: So they were hard on you?
Witness: Yes

124
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:30,958
Yes, their speech was harsh toward people

125
00:06:32,416 --> 00:06:33,625
Because they are criminals

126
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:38,041
Interviewer: Did you try to deal with them

127
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:41,125
And ask them to bring you something from outside the prison?

128
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:45,416
And if so, did they refuse?

129
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:48,791
Did you try to give them a certain sum of money?

130
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:53,875
So they would provide you a certain need or a comfort?

131
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:59,166
Yes, sometimes I needed biscuits or other things from outside

132
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,958
Or drinks and the like, and they would buy them for me

133
00:07:01,041 --> 00:07:05,125
I gave them money through the door slot to go, they would buy for me and return

134
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:10,750
Interviewer: Wasn’t your money with the deposited belongings they took from you?

135
00:07:10,791 --> 00:07:13,125
The deposited belongings, which were my ID card and watch

136
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:14,625
Were with them in the trailer

137
00:07:15,041 --> 00:07:16,125
Only the money was in my pocket

138
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:18,791
Interviewer: Didn’t they take the money from you?
Witness: No, they didn’t take it

139
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,291
I had money in my pocket

140
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:22,250
When I needed something, I asked their permission

141
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:24,875
And I said, sir, I want something

142
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:28,125
Could someone go to the grocery and buy for me

143
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,500
They would go, buy it for me, and bring it to me

144
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,541
Interviewer: Didn’t he get annoyed with you when you asked him?

145
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:36,041
I didn’t ask just anyone

146
00:07:36,125 --> 00:07:38,125
I asked the one who could tolerate me

147
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:43,125
Interviewer: Did you feel comfortable with any of the jailers?

148
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:44,666
In case a conversation happened between you

149
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:47,375
No, no, because I was afraid of them

150
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:52,375
Interviewer: Didn’t they try to reassure you, for example, and make you talk?

151
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:58,666
No, frankly you will not feel reassurance with them

152
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:03,916
Interviewer: Since you were in solitary, did you have a sense...

153
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:07,875
Of the people they brought for several hours, meaning for a short time?

154
00:08:08,166 --> 00:08:11,375
Did they send in one of their members as a spy?

155
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:15,375
Or did they assign people to question you or interrogate you inside?

156
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:17,625
Sometimes I felt that

157
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:21,250
I said to myself it is possible they would send one of the prisoners

158
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:25,416
To lure me with his questions, and I would answer them

159
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:29,166
I was careful of them

160
00:08:29,791 --> 00:08:34,041
Interviewer: Were there rooms next to you from which you heard voices?

161
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:36,125
Yes, I heard voices from here

162
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:38,666
There were some in the back

163
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:42,625
And in Mar Yousef Church

164
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,291
But we did not hear their voices because they were a bit far

165
00:08:46,375 --> 00:08:47,666
They would bring them here

166
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:51,375
When they whipped here, I heard the sound

167
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:55,666
They would bring whoever had prayer beads, or the like

168
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:57,375
They held them accountable by flogging them here

169
00:08:57,916 --> 00:09:00,000
Whoever they caught because of cigarettes

170
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:03,041
Or because of a satellite dish

171
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:07,125
They would punish them here, flogging them

172
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:10,375
Interviewer: Okay, regardless of the flogging that happened during the day

173
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,875
Did you hear sounds of torture at night?

174
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:16,416
Interviewer: Like screams from prisoners, for example? Witness:
Yes, a little

175
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,375
Interviewer: What were those sounds like?

176
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:24,125
When they caught someone who worked in the police

177
00:09:24,125 --> 00:09:26,916
Or in the National Guard, for example, or in the army

178
00:09:28,125 --> 00:09:30,041
They would bring him in, ISIS’s security group

179
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:35,041
From his screaming, it was clear they were beating him

180
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:37,625
Because we heard the sound from the window

181
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,666
Interviewer: Do you mean you didn’t see anyone being tortured?

182
00:09:42,666 --> 00:09:44,916
Interviewer: And you, were you not tortured in this prison?
Witness: No

183
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,416
Interviewer: So only the sounds you heard…

184
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:50,666
No, I didn’t see anything, they didn’t take me anywhere
